<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Before executing any printhead-calibration make sure the installation procedure has performed correctly. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DD58E455-BE06-4DCF-9042-B97A8A94B07A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">p 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To be able to determine the correct PAINT reference values a minimum number of nozzles needs to be operational. In case this calibration fails the data from a previous successful calibration is used or even the production data from this printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases this calibration is executed when a new printhead is placed into the printer. In case the filling of this new printhead was unsuccessful air might still be present in the printhead. The main goal of the mentioned procedure is to get possible air out of the printhead. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F2864082-F34C-4657-B37E-EA7C5343FE90.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
